# Memory Index

## Memory Governance
Before any persistent memory read, write, compress, or archive action, apply `memory-rule`.

Use `memory-rule` when:
- updating `MEMORY.md`
- writing to `notes/`
- promoting task facts into durable memory
- compressing or archiving completed work
- resolving conflicting preferences, rules, or corrections

## Sync Trigger
If durable local memory or managed workspace config changes need cross-device retention, use `sync-request` to create a sync request in `~/sync-queue/pending/` for Adam.
Do not run sync directly from this agent.

